                    <td><b>UX (user experience) design is about the entire user journey, making it smooth and enjoyable.  Imagine the overall flow of a restaurant visit.

                        UI (user interface) design is the look and feel, the buttons, menus, and visual elements you interact with.  Think of the interior design of the restaurant.
                        
                        Both UX and UI work together for a great digital product!</b></td>
                    <td><b>Planning and Design: This involves defining the software's purpose, features, and user interface.
